Nov 9 2009 	Good value great location!	The Belvedere is a great, no frills hotel located just steps from Paddington station. We stayed there as we had an early train to catch in the morning &amp; wanted a cheap hotel that was close to the station. We got exactly what we wanted. The rooms were simple but clean. Breakfast was simple and absolutely fine (but definitely not &quot;gourmet&quot;. We felt like we got good value for our money. Yes, the stairs were steep, so I would not recommend the hotel for the elderly or disabled. But for us (two able-bodied women in our forties) we were easily able to lug our bags up to the third floor. If you're looking for elegant or luxurious, you should pay the extra money &amp; go somewhere else. But if you're looking for basic, clean, convenient at a reasonable price, the Belvedere would fit the bill.	
