Apr 17 2009 	No Frills Hotel! Great Location! (From Heathrow)	The first thing that comes to mind about this hotel is the location. Take the Heathrow Express directly to Paddington. Its located just 300m or so from Paddington Station. Paddington (Westminster) is a quiet area and safe as well. The bus stop around the corner takes you to Oxford Circus and Piccadilly Cirus and drops you off right in front of the hotel! Overwise you can take to Tube.The room itself is very basic but clean. Bathroom is tiny, and for those people that are taller, you might have a problem with the shower and only a small bar of soap is provided, so make sure you bring your own shampoo etc. The heating is problematic as sometimes it cannot be switched on and reception assures us that they are on. Believe me, London can be very cold in the mornings.The breakfast is &quot;English Breakfast&quot; and thats all the choice that you get. Make sure that you go there early as the breakfast area is tiny and does not fit all the guests. Taller people should beware, as the stairs leading to the breakfast area is very cramped.In summary, I think that the main positive about this hotel is the location. This is what you are paying for! Everything else is very very basic.	
