Jun 27 2004	The most uncomfortable beds in the world!!	We stayed in this Hotel in February, 2004. For the price, the facilities were ok. The family room was good size and everything in the room was in working order. Miniscule bathroom. The breakfast was adequate and was a good start to the day. The rooms were cleaned daily. If it hadn't been for the horrible beds and really shabby linens this could be a reasonable hotel. The beds were like box springs. Low to the ground, lumpy and incredibly hard. Not what you want to come back to, after a long day of sight seeing. I got a creepy feeling about this place when I realized that they had misrepresented their breakfast room on the websites by using a picture of a nearby hotels' breakfast room. They have a decent country breakfast room so they should just display it and not try to fool people.	
